content:
Smart grocery assistant. Analyze this grocery list and suggest ideas.
{% if profile_context %}{{profile_context}}
{% endif %}
Grocery list: {{sections_text}}
{% if answers_text %}{{answers_text}}
{% endif %}
Steps: 1) Gap analysis — what's missing for complete recipes/preparations. 2) Cultural match — respect the cuisine patterns. 3) Recipe bridge — connect existing items into meal clusters. 4) Store layout — collect EVERY item name from clusters and ungrouped (both existing and new). Group them by grocery store aisle. The total item count in storeLayout must equal the sum of all items in clusters + ungrouped.

RESPOND WITH ONLY A JSON OBJECT. No explanations, no markdown, no thinking.

Return JSON:
{"reason": "1-sentence summary of analysis", "clusters": [{"name": "Meal Name", "emoji": "🍳", "desc": "1-sentence", "items": [{"name_en": "item", "existing": true/false, "why": "if new, why needed"}]}], "ungrouped": [{"name_en": "item", "existing": true}], "storeLayout": [{"category": "Aisle", "emoji": "🛒", "items": [{"name_en": "item", "existing": true/false}]}]}

Rules:
- 2-4 clusters, 3-6 NEW items total across all clusters
- Every existing item must appear in exactly one cluster or ungrouped
- Double-check: list all existing items from the grocery list. Each must appear in exactly one cluster or in ungrouped. None may be omitted.
- When user profile conflicts with answers, profile takes precedence (it represents persistent preferences)
- storeLayout must list EVERY item mentioned anywhere in clusters, ungrouped, or as new suggestions. Count them — the total should match.
